value.value: The absence of menses in a woman who has achieved reproductive age.
Acute form of gonococcal salpingitis.
Acute form of gonococcal prostatitis.
A morphologic variant of uterine corpus leiomyoma characterized by the presence of round or polygonal epithelioid smooth muscle cells forming clusters.
A senile cataract that involves the lens nucleus.
A non-Hodgkin or Hodgkin lymphoma that arises from the small intestine.
Idiopathic painful nonsuppurative swellings of one or more costal cartilages, especially of the second rib. The anterior chest pain may mimic that of coronary artery disease.
A atherosclerosis that involves the renal artery.
An instance of hypertrophic pyloric stenosis that is acquired during the lifetime of the individual.
A malignant neoplasm involving the anus
A neoplasm involving a abducens nerve.

A usually large cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma of B-cell phenotype, arising from the anus. Lymphomas originating from the anal region are rare in the general population, but they are seen with a higher frequency in HIV-positive patients, particularly homosexual men.
A non-Hodgkin or Hodgkin lymphoma that arises in the spinal cord as a primary lesion.
A melanoma (disease) that involves the spinal cord.
A sarcoma that arises from the spinal cord.

An abnormal accumulation of cerebrospinal fluid within the ventricles of the brain that occurs as a consequence of an obstruction at any location within the ventricular system that prevents cerebrospinal fluid flowing into the subarachnoid space.
A disease involving the optic choroid.
An instance of agammaglobulinemia that is present from birth.
Dermatomyositis in an adult.

A group of genetic disorders of the kidney tubules characterized by the accumulation of metabolically produced acids with elevated plasma chloride, hyperchloremic metabolic acidosis. Defective renal acidification of urine (proximal tubules) or low renal acid excretion (distal tubules) can lead to complications such as hypokalemia, hypercalcinuria with nephrolithiasis and nephrocalcinosis, and rickets.
Chronic form of perichondritis of auricle.
Otitis media that persists for at least six weeks, and that is associated with otorrhea through a perforated tympanic membrane.
A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder affecting the ureter.
Dysfunction of the pulmonary valve characterized by incomplete valve closure.
Cholangitis that is both sudden in onset and of a relatively short duration.
A disease involving the endocrine pancreas.
A non-neoplastic lesion that affects the vulva and is characterized by thinning or thickening of the skin and dryness.
The lack of vision. It is caused by neurological or physiological factors.
Acute form of thyroiditis (disease).
A dysentery that involves protozoan infection.
Chronic form of angle-closure glaucoma.
A congenital disorder characterized by the presence of extremely hypoplastic gonads preventing the development of secondary sex characteristics.
A lymphoma that involves the ureter.
A rare malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the pericardium.
Increased blood pressure in the arteries of the lungs; the etiology is unknown.
A cholesterol embolism that involves the kidney.
An episode of depression lasting two or more weeks without an intervening episode of mania.

A rare autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutations of the MUT, MMAA, MMAB, MMADHC, and MCEE genes. It is characterized by abnormalities in the metabolism of lipids and proteins. Signs and symptoms usually appear early in life and vary from mild to life threatening. They include vomiting, dehydration, hypotonia, developmental delays, hepatomegaly, lethargy, intellectual disabilities, and chronic kidney disease.
A benign lesion composed of dilated lymphatic channels. Painless swelling is the usual clinical manifestation.

label.value: autosomal recessive Ehlers-Danlos syndrome, vascular type

value.value: The rare autosomal recessive form of the vascular type of Ehlers-Danlos syndrome. vEDS is almost always inherited in an autosomal dominant manner but rare examples of biallelic inheritance have been reported.
A group of sporadic and inherited neurodegenerative disorders affecting the cerebellum, pons, and inferior olives.

A disorder characterized by behavioral and/or psychological abnormalities, often accompanied by physical symptoms. The symptoms may cause clinically significant distress or impairment in social and occupational areas of functioning. Representative examples include anxiety disorders, cognitive disorders, mood disorders and schizophrenia.
Infection with the organism Candida.

A diverse category of psychiatric disorders characterized by behavior that deviates markedly from the expectations of the individual's culture; this pattern of deviation is pervasive and inflexible and is stable over time. The behavioral pattern negatively interferes with relationships and work.
Chronic form of gonococcal cervicitis.
Chronic inflammation of the cervix.
